description: Wealthsimple Inc. announced its first credit card and a line of credit Wednesday as it ramps up efforts to challenge the dominance of Canada's big banks.
title: Wealthsimple launches credit card, new line of credit to challenge big banks

description: The parliamentary budget officer says an eligible first-time homebuyer would save an average of $26,832 in sales tax on the price of a newly built home under Ottawa's latest housing proposal.
title: GST rebate on new homes would save typical first-time buyer $27K: Budget officer

description: Holding the country together has always been one of the primary tasks of a Canadian prime minister. But it's fair to say that responsibility may weigh heavier on Mark Carney than it has on any prime minister since Jean Chrétien.
title: Mark Carney has a national unity problem. A Liberal voice in Calgary might help

description: Former deputy finance minister and business executive Michael Sabia has been named the next head of Canada’s public service.
title: Former deputy minister, businessman Michael Sabia named next Privy Council clerk

description: Israeli gunfire and airstrikes killed at least 60 Palestinians in Gaza on Wednesday, most of them near an aid site operated by the U.S- and Israeli-backed Gaza Humanitarian Foundation in the center of the enclave, local health officials said.
title: At least 25 Palestinians killed in Israeli gunfire near aid site, local medics say

description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Wednesday that the bodies of two hostages had been recovered from Gaza by the military and the domestic intelligence agency, the Shin Bet.
title: Israeli PM says bodies of 2 more hostages recovered from Gaza

description: The RCMP provided an update Wednesday on their investigation into the disappearance of Lilly Sullivan, 6, and her four-year-old brother Jack. They vanished from their home on May 2.
title: All scenarios being considered, RCMP say 5 weeks after N.S. children disappeared

description: Disney and Universal have filed a copyright lawsuit against popular artificial intelligence image-generator Midjourney, marking the first time major Hollywood companies have entered the legal battle over generative AI.
title: Disney and Universal sue AI firm Midjourney for copyright infringement

description: Former movie mogul Harvey Weinstein was convicted Wednesday of one of the top charges in his sex crimes retrial but acquitted of another, and jurors were as yet unable to reach a verdict on a third charge.
title: Harvey Weinstein guilty on 1 charge in sex crimes retrial

description: A statement from Public Safety Canada says more than 12,000 guns have been bought back from businesses in the first phase of the program. But the federal department says it is still working to identify which, if any, will go to Ukraine.
title: No banned firearms have been sent to Ukraine, despite government promise

description: U.S. President Donald Trump has said that without a military response, Los Angeles would have been "obliterated" due to protests over immigration raids. At least so far, the protests have not led to life-threatening injuries.
title: Days into L.A. immigration raid protests, it appears journalists are bearing the brunt of injuries

description: A 16-year-old boy accused of seriously injuring another student with a sword at Brandon's Neelin High School had plans for more victims but was stopped by the swift actions of officials and officers, the southwestern Manitoba city's police chief says.
title: More victims, bloodshed were intended in sword attack at Brandon high school: police

description: Brian Wilson, whose virtuoso vocal and musical arrangements led the Beach Boys to commercial and critical success, making them one of America's most influential bands, before personal demons waylaid his life and career for several years, has died.
title: Beach Boys visionary Brian Wilson dead at 82

description: Khaby Lame, the world's most popular TikTok personality, with more than 162 million followers, has left the U.S. after being detained by immigration agents in Las Vegas for allegedly overstaying his visa.
title: Khaby Lame has the most followers on TikTok. ICE detained him — and now he's left the U.S.

description: Canada is expected to see a warmer-than-usual summer with dry conditions and severe wildfires in Western Canada, says Environment and Climate Change Canada's summer forecast.
title: Hotter-than-normal summer forecast in most of Canada

description: Hundreds of fans gathered in the early morning hours to catch a glimpse of K-pop superstars Jimin and Jung Kook, the latest and final members of BTS to be discharged from South Korea's mandatory military service.
title: Fans celebrate as BTS stars Jimin, Jung Kook end mandatory South Korea military service

description: We're back at Superior Court in London, Ont., to cover the latest developments from the sexual assault trial of five former world junior hockey players.
title: Defence teams continue closing arguments at sex assault trial of ex-Hockey Canada world junior players

description: Ottawa's efforts to prepare the country for the impacts of climate change have stumbled out of the gate, Canada's environment commissioner says.
title: Ottawa's plan for climate change adaptation is falling short, report says

description: U.K. Prime Minister Keir Starmer will arrive in Ottawa Saturday for a visit with Prime Minister Mark Carney on his way to the G7 leaders’ summit in Kananaskis, Alta.
title: U.K. Prime Minister Keir Starmer to visit Ottawa on his way to G7 summit in Alberta

description: Billionaire businessman Elon Musk said on Wednesday he regretted some of the posts he made last week about U.S. President Donald Trump as they had gone "too far."
title: Musk says he regrets some X posts he made about Trump

description: A judge found Ken Porter sexually touched teenage boys for his own gratification under the guise of athletic massages while he was their coach in the 1970s.
title: Former Edmonton track coach found guilty of historic sexual offences against teen athletes

description: Charges have been stayed against a man accused of threatening to post intimate images online unless he was paid money by victims across four provinces, after prosecutors decided not to proceed with the case because of victims' "unwillingness to relive the experience by testifying."
title: Charges stayed against Winnipeg man accused in sextortion case across 4 provinces

description: The group Doctors 4 Cambridge invited medical students to the city as part of the Rural Ontario Medical Placement week with a goal of convincing them to move to the community after graduation. The week included more than just showing them where they could work, but also fine dining, entertainment and more.
title: From clinics to culinary tours to laser tag: How this Ontario city is wooing future doctors

description: Some people forced from their homes by wildfires in northern Saskatchewan will soon start making their way home, as conditions improve in the La Ronge area.
title: La Ronge evacuees to begin returning home Thursday

description: Lyme disease, a potentially debilitating tick-borne infection if it is left untreated, is a growing problem in parts of Canada, with thousands of reported cases. But could there soon be a vaccine?
title: How close are we to getting a vaccine for Lyme disease?

description: The family of a Smiths Falls, Ont., woman is demanding justice after a video surfaced online that appears to show the woman being dragged from a police cruiser and held to the ground after her arrest.
title: Family of woman seen dragged from police cruiser in Smith Falls, Ont., calling for justice

description: Live-action adaptations usually feel like soulless, board-room directed cash-grabs engineered for mass appeal. Which raises the question: Why is the new How to Train Your Dragon sort of … actually good?
title: How to Train Your Dragon: We can get one good live-action adaptation. As a treat

description: There's a quiet and mysterious move afoot to push Premier Doug Ford's Ontario PC government to adopt more fiscally conservative policies.
title: Who's behind 'Project Ontario,' the group pushing Doug Ford to be more conservative?
